cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE 

The paper deals with the problem of Monocular Visual Odometry using a Deep Learning-based framework, which is a subfield of computer vision and robotics. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) and cs.RO (Robotics) are the most likely categories. The paper also proposes a Convolutional Neural Network architecture, which falls under the subfield of machine learning, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely categories as well. Finally, the paper uses deep learning techniques, which is a subfield of neural networks, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) a possible category.
